            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0049.agda" type="external">erct-0049.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Any <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="//erct/erct-001T" type="local">propositional map</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-003K.xml" title="Embedding" addr="//erct/erct-003K" type="local">embedding</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>18</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>9205</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">//erct/unstable/494</fr:addr><fr:route>foreign-erct-unstable-494.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Fixing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:A]]></fr:tex> we must show that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{f}\colon  x = y \to  fx=fy]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000W.xml" title="Inverse" addr="//erct/erct-000W" type="local">invertible</fr:link>. By <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-002C.xml" title="From quasi-inverses to coherent inverses" addr="//erct/erct-002C" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-002C" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-002D.xml" title="From biinverses to quasi-inverses" addr="//erct/erct-002D" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-002D" /></fr:link>, it suffices to exhibit a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000U.xml" title="Biinverse" addr="//erct/erct-000U" type="local">biinverse</fr:link> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{f}]]></fr:tex> (it is convenient that the underlying maps of the <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="//erct/erct-000Y" type="local">section</fr:link> and <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="//erct/erct-000Y" type="local">retraction</fr:link> need not be identical).</fr:p>

 <fr:p>We first define the <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="//erct/erct-000Y" type="local">sections</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{x,y}\colon  fx = fy \to  x = y]]></fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is assumed to be <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="//erct/erct-001T" type="local">propositional</fr:link>, we have by <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001R.xml" title="Path object structure on fibers" addr="//erct/erct-001R" type="local">Example <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-001R" /></fr:link> an assignment <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi _{x,y}: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,\mathsf {refl}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\cong _{\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen fx\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y,h^{-1}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex>. We therefore define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{x,y}h :\equiv  
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \phi _{x,y}h\right \rparen \mathclose {}
.1]]></fr:tex>; the witness of <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="//erct/erct-000Y" type="local">sectionhood</fr:link> can be constructed using <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \phi _{x,y}h\right \rparen \mathclose {}
.2]]></fr:tex> modulo some identification algebra.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>To construct the <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="//erct/erct-000Y" type="local">retractions</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r_{x,y}\colon  fx=fy\to  x = y]]></fr:tex>, we note by our assumption that we have an assignment <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\psi _{x,y}:\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,\mathsf {refl}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 =_{\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen fx\right \rparen \mathclose {}
} 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y,h^{-1}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex>, and we define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r_{x,y}h :\equiv  \mathsf {act}_{-.1}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \psi _{x,y}h\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex>. It remains to show that for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[h\colon  x =y]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{-.1}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \psi _{x,y}h\right \rparen \mathclose {}
=h]]></fr:tex>. By induction on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[h]]></fr:tex> it suffices to show that for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x:A]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{-.1}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \psi _{x,x}\mathsf {refl}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 = \mathsf {refl}]]></fr:tex>. We will deduce that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\psi _{x,x}\mathsf {refl} = \mathsf {refl}]]></fr:tex> from our assumption that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="//erct/erct-001T" type="local">propositional</fr:link> and thus <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="//erct/erct-001T" type="local">fibred in sets</fr:link> via <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001L.xml" title="Propositions are sets" addr="//erct/erct-001L" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-001L" /></fr:link>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
