   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>31</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>9197</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">//erct/unstable/471</fr:addr><fr:route>foreign-erct-unstable-471.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>We must show that each <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001Q.xml" title="Fiber" addr="//erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fiber</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001H.xml" title="Contractible type" addr="//erct/erct-001H" type="local">proposition</fr:link>; in fact, each <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001Q.xml" title="Fiber" addr="//erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fiber</fr:link> is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="//erct/erct-001I" type="local">contractible</fr:link> as <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-002N.xml" title="Biinvertible maps are contractible" addr="//erct/erct-002N" type="local">biinvertible maps are contractible</fr:link>, and <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001K.xml" title="Contractible types are propositions" addr="//erct/erct-001K" type="local">contractible types are propositions</fr:link>.</fr:p>
